.TH "ata_ehi_push_desc" 9 "ata_ehi_push_desc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_ehi_push_desc \- push error description with separator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ata_ehi_push_desc
.BI "(struct ata_eh_info *ehi "  ","
.BI "const char *fmt "  ","
.BI "... "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ehi" 12
target EHI
.IP "fmt" 12
printf format string

Format string according to \fIfmt\fP and append it to \fIehi->desc\fP.
If \fIehi->desc\fP is not empty, ", " is added in-between.

LOCKING:
spin_lock_irqsave(host lock)
.IP "..." 12
variable arguments
